Aggregated Table Widget

The aggregated table widget allows you to generates a report showing the number of objects of respective type/s grouped by a certain property.

 

Note: To see how to insert and configure the widget look 

Aggregated Table View

 

  1.  A table with two columns is inserted into the document.
  2.  The first column is "Number".  Each row of the table displays the number of objects from the search result that have the value of the property selected for grouping.
  3.  The second column has the name of the property selected for grouping (in the example - Sub-classification). Each row shows the value of the property.
    If a property with code list values is selected for grouping, and there are 0 objects for some of the values, then there will be no rows for these values in the aggregated table.
  4.  At the bottom of the table is the total number of records counted.
